#150030
Pine Lodge~
Built around the massive bole of an old oak tree, the building is
circular in shape.  Evenly spaced roughly hewn beams encircled with ivy
meet the distance from tree to wall hatching bound by the same ivy fills
the spaces.  The Tree must be rather ancient judging from its size, as
many trees of great age the heart has hollowed out making for a
convenient hearth.  On the opposite side of the tree a rope ladder
reaches up to the ceiling, a circular portal gives access to the roof. 
The walls are made of pine, lending a fresh smell to the room, muted by
the smell of various animals.  Several paintings adorn the wall, either
showing hectic battle scenes or of tranquil nature settings, there is
also the obligatory five point white stag trophy head.  There is no
furniture to speak of, but the floor is practically blanketed in several
piles of bearskins that seem to serve for both sitting and bedding.  In
the corner lies a pile of adventuring equipment - coils of rope, climbing
spikes, a shovel and a pickaxe.
