#150043
A Cozy Home Inside a Large Tree~
Stepping inside, you notice that the whole tree is hollow and has been
turned into a large cozy room.  Intricate swirling designs of various
birds and animals have been painted in bright colors over the walls.  An
attractive stone fireplace has been constructed against the wall to the
west, providing a roaring hot fire for cold winter days, and a large
colourful rug lies on the floor infront of it.  In the north west corner
of the room a small spiral staircase leads higher up into the tree, and a
high glass door behind it provides an exit out into the backyard to the
west.  Large windows in the north and south walls provide light for the
room.  Vines of wisteria growing outside partially cover the windows
causing the light to enter in sparkles as the sunlight shines through.  A
large dining table has been placed, with a chair either end of it, near
the window to the south.  A small window in the east wall next to the
doorway looks out to the front garden and the road of Zirnath.
